{
  "stem": "25651.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, you know, as a child of four or five, how can you understand anti-Semitism?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I asked my mother why the children wouldn't play with me, she said, you'll understand this later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was one of the phrases that my mother used quite a bit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I hated this phrase as a child, you will understand it later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because, in fact, it's very difficult to understand.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was talking about my mother's benevolence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The other benevolence was that Jewish people from Poland would come through our town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our town is in northeastern Moravia, so there were these expeditions to go and collect money for the Yeshivat in Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were all people in kaftans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were all very colorful, you know, bearded, pious men with hats.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Many had distinct red hair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was even a group that used to come on bicycles, which my father used to call [GERMAN], which means the motorized ones.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father used to say that if-- if in a few days no beggars or no Jewish men would come asking for alms, my mother would go out of town looking for them, you know, like where are they?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the conversations were always in Yiddish between my mother and these men.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were always men.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- you know, lots of people are put off by the kaftan and the-- and the garb and the behavior of [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never had that feeling, because my mother was so at one with these people, so I found them colorful.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some of them would stay.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, these people were so religious that even in our kosher house-- which was strictly kosher, and they could see the way that my mother spoke that it was kosher.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
